n = int(input())
a = [int(x) for x in input().split()] # list comprehension

def remove_duplicates(a):
    b = []
    for i in range(len(a)):
        if a[i] in b:
            continue
        else:
            b.append(a[i])
    return b

b = remove_duplicates(a)
print(len(b))
print(*b) # print all elements of the list


from collections import deque

def main():
    n = int(input())
    nums = deque()
    for i in range(n):
        nums.append(int(input()))
    nums = list(set(nums))
    print(len(nums))
    print(*nums)

main()


from collections import deque

def main():
    n = int(input())
    nums = deque()
    for i in range(n):
        nums.append(int(input()))
    nums = list(dict.fromkeys(nums)) # remove duplicates
    print(len(nums))
    print(*nums)

main()

from collections import deque

def main():
    n = int(input())
    nums = deque()
    for i in range(n):
        nums.append(int(input()))
    nums = list(dict.fromkeys(nums)) # оставляем только уникальные элементы
